@DATABASE "ppmnorm.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Converter: ColorContrast [ppmnorm]"
@TOC "Converter.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}ColorContrast@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Normalize the contrast in a portable pixmap.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads a portable pixmap as input. Normalizes the contrast by forcing the lightest pixels to white,
the darkest pixels to black, and linearly rescaling the ones in between;
and produces a portable pixmap as output. Works by computing the realtive grey-level of each pixel,
and uses those values to scale the RGB levels.@{LINE}
@{PAR}By default, the darkest 2 percent of all pixels are mapped to black,
and the lightest 1 percent are mapped to white. You can override these percentages.
If you want to lighten the image, then set blackness to 0 and just fiddle with whiteness;
similarly, to darken the image, set whiteness to 0 and play with blackness.@{LINE}
@{PAR}See also @{" GreyContrast " LINK "pgmnorm.guide/MAIN"} and @{" ColorSaturation " LINK "ppmbrighten.guide/MAIN"}.@{LINE}
@{PAR}[@{B}ppmnorm@{UB}] @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}Copyright (C) 1991 by Wilson H. Bent. Jr. @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
